# Coding Style

## Language

- All source code is **plain JavaScript** (ES modules). No TypeScript in `src/`.
- Type declarations live separately in `types/` and are generated via `npm run generate:types`.

## Component format

- Components are **plain JS objects** with `name`, `mixins`, `props`, `emits`, `setup()`.
- No `.vue` SFCs in `src/components/`. Templates live in `themes/`.
- Use composition API (`setup()`) for all new behavior. Mixins are for shared prop declarations only.

## Composable pattern

```js
export default function useMyFeature(props, context, dependencies) {
  const { form$, el$, path } = dependencies

  const myComputed = computed(() => { ... })

  return { myComputed }
}
```

- Accept `(props, context, dependencies)` — dependencies come from earlier features in the pipeline.
- Return a plain object of refs/computed/methods to merge into the element instance.
- Export named variants when multiple element types need different behavior (e.g. `text`, `list`, `group`).

## Naming

- Element components: `<Name>Element.js` (e.g. `TextElement.js`, `SelectElement.js`)
- Composables: `use<Feature>.js` (e.g. `useValidation.js`, `useValue.js`)
- Services: lowercase directory with `index.js` (e.g. `services/validation/index.js`)
- Utils: camelCase filename matching the exported function

## ESLint

Lint with `npm run lint`. Config is in `eslint.config.mjs`. Fix auto-fixable issues with `npx eslint src/ --fix`.

## Vue 2 + 3 dual support

The library supports both Vue 2 and Vue 3. The Vue 2 build uses `rollup.vue2.config.js` with pre/post build scripts. When writing composables, avoid Vue 3-only APIs that don't have Vue 2 equivalents unless gated.
